    "First curator of classical art at the Walters Gallery, Baltimore.": [],
    "Hill studied at Vassar (class of 1928) and continued Johns Hopkins University, graduating in 1933.": [],
    "Her dissertation, on Greek pottery, was titled <em>Conventions of Attic Black-figured Drawing</em>, written under <a href=\"/robinsond\">David Moore Robinson</a> (1880-1958).": [],
    "Hill was immediately hired by the nascent Walters Art Gallery.": [],
    "Henry Walters had bequeathed over 23,000 art works in 1931 to the city.": [],
    "Other curators hired for the new museum included <a href=\"/minerd\">Dorothy E. Miner</a>.": [],
    "Hill set about cataloging the collection of ancient art, rising to curator of Classical Art in 1937.": [],
    "In 1948 she began editing the <em>Journal of the Walters Art Gallery</em>.": [
